461Co 1:1 Paul, called [as] an apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God, and Sosthenes our brother,
461Co 1:2 to the church of God which is at Corinth, to those who have been sanctified in Christ Jesus, saints by calling, with all who in every place call upon the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, their [Lord] and ours：
461Co 1:3 Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
461Co 1:4 I thank my God always concerning you, for the grace of God which was given you in Christ Jesus,
461Co 1:5 that in everything you were enriched in Him, in all speech and all knowledge,
461Co 1:6 even as the testimony concerning Christ was confirmed in you,
461Co 1:7 so that you are not lacking in any gift, awaiting eagerly the revelation of our Lord Jesus Christ,
461Co 1:8 who shall also confirm you to the end, blameless in the day of our Lord Jesus Christ.
461Co 1:9 God is faithful, through whom you were called into fellowship with His Son, Jesus Christ our Lord.
461Co 1:10 Now I exhort you, brethren, by the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, that you all agree, and there be no divisions among you, but you be made complete in the same mind and in the same judgment.
461Co 1:11 For I have been informed concerning you, my brethren, by Chloe's [people,] that there are quarrels among you.
461Co 1:12 Now I mean this, that each one of you is saying, "I am of Paul," and "I of Apollos," and "I of Cephas," and "I of Christ."
461Co 1:13 Has Christ been divided? Paul was not crucified for you, was he? Or were you baptized in the name of Paul?
461Co 1:14 I thank God that I baptized none of you except Crispus and Gaius,
461Co 1:15 that no man should say you were baptized in my name.
461Co 1:16 Now I did baptize also the household of Stephanas; beyond that, I do not know whether I baptized any other.
461Co 1:17 For Christ did not send me to baptize, but to preach the gospel, not in cleverness of speech, that the cross of Christ should not be made void.
461Co 1:18 For the word of the cross is to those who are perishing foolishness, but to us who are being saved it is the power of God.
461Co 1:19 For it is written, "I WILL DESTROY THE WISDOM OF THE WISE, AND THE CLEVERNESS OF THE CLEVER I WILL SET ASIDE."
461Co 1:20 Where is the wise man? Where is the scribe? Where is the debater of this age? Has not God made foolish the wisdom of the world?
461Co 1:21 For since in the wisdom of God the world through its wisdom did not [come to] know God, God was well-pleased through the foolishness of the message preached to save those who believe.
461Co 1:22 For indeed Jews ask for signs, and Greeks search for wisdom;
461Co 1:23 but we preach Christ crucified, to Jews a stumbling block, and to Gentiles foolishness,
461Co 1:24 but to those who are the called, both Jews and Greeks, Christ the power of God and the wisdom of God.
461Co 1:25 Because the foolishness of God is wiser than men, and the weakness of God is stronger than men.
461Co 1:26 For consider your calling, brethren, that there were not many wise according to the flesh, not many mighty, not many noble;
461Co 1:27 but God has chosen the foolish things of the world to shame the wise, and God has chosen the weak things of the world to shame the things which are strong,
461Co 1:28 and the base things of the world and the despised, God has chosen, the things that are not, that He might nullify the things that are,
461Co 1:29 that no man should boast before God.
461Co 1:30 But by His doing you are in Christ Jesus, who became to us wisdom from God, and righteousness and sanctification, and redemption,
461Co 1:31 that, just as it is written, "LET HIM WHO BOASTS, BOAST IN THE LORD."
461Co 2:1 And when I came to you, brethren, I did not come with superiority of speech or of wisdom, proclaiming to you the testimony of God.
461Co 2:2 For I determined to know nothing among you except Jesus Christ, and Him crucified.
461Co 2:3 And I was with you in weakness and in fear and in much trembling.
461Co 2:4 And my message and my preaching were not in persuasive words of wisdom, but in demonstration of the Spirit and of power,
461Co 2:5 that your faith should not rest on the wisdom of men, but on the power of God.
461Co 2:6 Yet we do speak wisdom among those who are mature; a wisdom, however, not of this age, nor of the rulers of this age, who are passing away;
461Co 2:7 but we speak God's wisdom in a mystery, the hidden [wisdom,] which God predestined before the ages to our glory;
461Co 2:8 [the wisdom] which none of the rulers of this age has understood; for if they had understood it, they would not have crucified the Lord of glory;
461Co 2:9 but just as it is written, "THINGS WHICH EYE HAS NOT SEEN AND EAR HAS NOT HEARD, AND [which] HAVE NOT ENTERED THE HEART OF MAN, ALL THAT GOD HAS PREPARED FOR THOSE WHO LOVE HIM."
461Co 2:10 For to us God revealed [them] through the Spirit; for the Spirit searches all things, even the depths of God.
461Co 2:11 For who among men knows the [thoughts] of a man except the spirit of the man, which is in him? Even so the [thoughts] of God no one knows except the Spirit of God.
461Co 2:12 Now we have received, not the spirit of the world, but the Spirit who is from God, that we might know the things freely given to us by God,
461Co 2:13 which things we also speak, not in words taught by human wisdom, but in those taught by the Spirit, combining spiritual [thoughts] with spiritual [words.]
461Co 2:14 But a natural man does not accept the things of the Spirit of God; for they are foolishness to him, and he cannot understand them, because they are spiritually appraised.
461Co 2:15 But he who is spiritual appraises all things, yet he himself is appraised by no man.
461Co 2:16 For WHO HAS KNOWN THE MIND OF THE LORD, THAT HE SHOULD INSTRUCT HIM? But we have the mind of Christ.
461Co 3:1 And I, brethren, could not speak to you as to spiritual men, but as to men of flesh, as to babes in Christ.
461Co 3:2 I gave you milk to drink, not solid food; for you were not yet able [ to receive it.] Indeed, even now you are not yet able,
461Co 3:3 for you are still fleshly. For since there is jealousy and strife among you, are you not fleshly, and are you not walking like mere men?
461Co 3:4 For when one says, "I am of Paul," and another, "I am of Apollos," are you not [mere] men?
461Co 3:5 What then is Apollos? And what is Paul? Servants through whom you believed, even as the Lord gave [opportunity] to each one.
461Co 3:6 I planted, Apollos watered, but God was causing the growth.
461Co 3:7 So then neither the one who plants nor the one who waters is anything, but God who causes the growth.
461Co 3:8 Now he who plants and he who waters are one; but each will receive his own reward according to his own labor.
461Co 3:9 For we are God's fellow workers; you are God's field, God's building.
461Co 3:10 According to the grace of God which was given to me, as a wise master builder I laid a foundation, and another is building upon it. But let each man be careful how he builds upon it.
461Co 3:11 For no man can lay a foundation other than the one which is laid, which is Jesus Christ.
461Co 3:12 Now if any man builds upon the foundation with gold, silver, precious stones, wood, hay, straw,
461Co 3:13 each man's work will become evident; for the day will show it, because it is [to be] revealed with fire; and the fire itself will test the quality of each man's work.
461Co 3:14 If any man's work which he has built upon it remains, he shall receive a reward.
461Co 3:15 If any man's work is burned up, he shall suffer loss; but he himself shall be saved, yet so as through fire.
461Co 3:16 Do you not know that you are a temple of God, and [that] the Spirit of God dwells in you?
461Co 3:17 If any man destroys the temple of God, God will destroy him, for the temple of God is holy, and that is what you are.
461Co 3:18 Let no man deceive himself. If any man among you thinks that he is wise in this age, let him become foolish that he may become wise.
461Co 3:19 For the wisdom of this world is foolishness before God. For it is written, "[He is] THE ONE WHO CATCHES THE WISE IN THEIR CRAFTINESS";
461Co 3:20 and again, "THE LORD KNOWS THE REASONINGS of the wise, THAT THEY ARE USELESS."
461Co 3:21 So then let no one boast in men. For all things belong to you,
461Co 3:22 whether Paul or Apollos or Cephas or the world or life or death or things present or things to come; all things belong to you,
461Co 3:23 and you belong to Christ; and Christ belongs to God.
461Co 4:1 Let a man regard us in this manner, as servants of Christ, and stewards of the mysteries of God.
461Co 4:2 In this case, moreover, it is required of stewards that one be found trustworthy.
461Co 4:3 But to me it is a very small thing that I should be examined by you, or by [any] human court; in fact, I do not even examine myself.
461Co 4:4 For I am conscious of nothing against myself, yet I am not by this acquitted; but the one who examines me is the Lord.
461Co 4:5 Therefore do not go on passing judgment before the time, [but wait] until the Lord comes who will both bring to light the things hidden in the darkness and disclose the motives of [men's] hearts; and then each man's praise will come to him from God.
461Co 4:6 Now these things, brethren, I have figuratively applied to myself and Apollos for your sakes, that in us you might learn not to exceed what is written, in order that no one of you might become arrogant in behalf of one against the other.
461Co 4:7 For who regards you as superior? And what do you have that you did not receive? But if you did receive it, why do you boast as if you had not received it?
461Co 4:8 You are already filled, you have already become rich, you have become kings without us; and [I] would indeed that you had become kings so that we also might reign with you.
461Co 4:9 For, I think, God has exhibited us apostles last of all, as men condemned to death; because we have become a spectacle to the world, both to angels and to men.
461Co 4:10 We are fools for Christ's sake, but you are prudent in Christ; we are weak, but you are strong; you are distinguished, but we are without honor.
461Co 4:11 To this present hour we are both hungry and thirsty, and are poorly clothed, and are roughly treated, and are homeless;
461Co 4:12 and we toil, working with our own hands; when we are reviled, we bless; when we are persecuted, we endure;
461Co 4:13 when we are slandered, we try to conciliate; we have become as the scum of the world, the dregs of all things, [even] until now.
461Co 4:14 I do not write these things to shame you, but to admonish you as my beloved children.
461Co 4:15 For if you were to have countless tutors in Christ, yet [you would] not [have] many fathers; for in Christ Jesus I became your father through the gospel.
461Co 4:16 I exhort you therefore, be imitators of me.
461Co 4:17 For this reason I have sent to you Timothy, who is my beloved and faithful child in the Lord, and he will remind you of my ways which are in Christ, just as I teach everywhere in every church.
461Co 4:18 Now some have become arrogant, as though I were not coming to you.
461Co 4:19 But I will come to you soon, if the Lord wills, and I shall find out, not the words of those who are arrogant, but their power.
461Co 4:20 For the kingdom of God does not consist in words, but in power.
461Co 4:21 What do you desire? Shall I come to you with a rod or with love and a spirit of gentleness?
461Co 5:1 It is actually reported that there is immorality among you, and immorality of such a kind as does not exist even among the Gentiles, that someone has his father's wife.
461Co 5:2 And you have become arrogant, and have not mourned instead, in order that the one who had done this deed might be removed from your midst.
461Co 5:3 For I, on my part, though absent in body but present in spirit, have already judged him who has so committed this, as though I were present.
461Co 5:4 In the name of our Lord Jesus, when you are assembled, and I with you in spirit, with the power of our Lord Jesus,
461Co 5:5 [I have decided] to deliver such a one to Satan for the destruction of his flesh, that his spirit may be saved in the day of the Lord Jesus.
461Co 5:6 Your boasting is not good. Do you not know that a little leaven leavens the whole lump [of dough]?
461Co 5:7 Clean out the old leaven, that you may be a new lump, just as you are [in fact] unleavened. For Christ our Passover also has been sacrificed.
461Co 5:8 Let us therefore celebrate the feast, not with old leaven, nor with the leaven of malice and wickedness, but with the unleavened bread of sincerity and truth.
461Co 5:9 I wrote you in my letter not to associate with immoral people;
461Co 5:10 I [did] not at all [mean] with the immoral people of this world, or with the covetous and swindlers, or with idolaters; for then you would have to go out of the world.
461Co 5:11 But actually, I wrote to you not to associate with any so-called brother if he should be an immoral person, or covetous, or an idolater, or a reviler, or a drunkard, or a swindler-- not even to eat with such a one.
461Co 5:12 For what have I to do with judging outsiders? Do you not judge those who are within [the church]?
461Co 5:13 But those who are outside, God judges. REMOVE THE WICKED MAN FROM AMONG YOURSELVES.
461Co 6:1 Does any one of you, when he has a case against his neighbor, dare to go to law before the unrighteous, and not before the saints?
461Co 6:2 Or do you not know that the saints will judge the world? And if the world is judged by you, are you not competent [to constitute] the smallest law courts?
461Co 6:3 Do you not know that we shall judge angels? How much more, matters of this life?
461Co 6:4 If then you have law courts dealing with matters of this life, do you appoint them as judges who are of no account in the church?
461Co 6:5 I say [this] to your shame. [Is it] so, [that] there is not among you one wise man who will be able to decide between his brethren,
461Co 6:6 but brother goes to law with brother, and that before unbelievers?
461Co 6:7 Actually, then, it is already a defeat for you, that you have lawsuits with one another. Why not rather be wronged? Why not rather be defrauded?
461Co 6:8 On the contrary, you yourselves wrong and defraud, and that [your] brethren.
461Co 6:9 Or do you not know that the unrighteous shall not inherit the kingdom of God? Do not be deceived; neither fornicators, nor idolaters, nor adulterers, nor effeminate, nor homosexuals,
461Co 6:10 nor thieves, nor [the] covetous, nor drunkards, nor revilers, nor swindlers, shall inherit the kingdom of God.
461Co 6:11 And such were some of you; but you were washed, but you were sanctified, but you were justified in the name of the Lord Jesus Christ, and in the Spirit of our God.
461Co 6:12 All things are lawful for me, but not all things are profitable. All things are lawful for me, but I will not be mastered by anything.
461Co 6:13 Food is for the stomach, and the stomach is for food; but God will do away with both of them. Yet the body is not for immorality, but for the Lord; and the Lord is for the body.
461Co 6:14 Now God has not only raised the Lord, but will also raise us up through His power.
461Co 6:15 Do you not know that your bodies are members of Christ? Shall I then take away the members of Christ and make them members of a harlot? May it never be!
461Co 6:16 Or do you not know that the one who joins himself to a harlot is one body [with her]? For He says, "THE TWO WILL BECOME ONE FLESH."
461Co 6:17 But the one who joins himself to the Lord is one spirit [with Him.]
461Co 6:18 Flee immorality. Every [other] sin that a man commits is outside the body, but the immoral man sins against his own body.
461Co 6:19 Or do you not know that your body is a temple of the Holy Spirit who is in you, whom you have from God, and that you are not your own?
461Co 6:20 For you have been bought with a price： therefore glorify God in your body.
461Co 7:1 Now concerning the things about which you wrote, it is good for a man not to touch a woman.
461Co 7:2 But because of immoralities, let each man have his own wife, and let each woman have her own husband.
461Co 7:3 Let the husband fulfill his duty to his wife, and likewise also the wife to her husband.
461Co 7:4 The wife does not have authority over her own body, but the husband [ does]; and likewise also the husband does not have authority over his own body, but the wife [does.]
461Co 7:5 Stop depriving one another, except by agreement for a time that you may devote yourselves to prayer, and come together again lest Satan tempt you because of your lack of self-control.
461Co 7:6 But this I say by way of concession, not of command.
461Co 7:7 Yet I wish that all men were even as I myself am. However, each man has his own gift from God, one in this manner, and another in that.
461Co 7:8 But I say to the unmarried and to widows that it is good for them if they remain even as I.
461Co 7:9 But if they do not have self-control, let them marry; for it is better to marry than to burn.
461Co 7:10 But to the married I give instructions, not I, but the Lord, that the wife should not leave her husband
461Co 7:11 (but if she does leave, let her remain unmarried, or else be reconciled to her husband), and that the husband should not send his wife away.
461Co 7:12 But to the rest I say, not the Lord, that if any brother has a wife who is an unbeliever, and she consents to live with him, let him not send her away.
461Co 7:13 And a woman who has an unbelieving husband, and he consents to live with her, let her not send her husband away.
461Co 7:14 For the unbelieving husband is sanctified through his wife, and the unbelieving wife is sanctified through her believing husband; for otherwise your children are unclean, but now they are holy.
461Co 7:15 Yet if the unbelieving one leaves, let him leave; the brother or the sister is not under bondage in such [cases,] but God has called us to peace.
461Co 7:16 For how do you know, O wife, whether you will save your husband? Or how do you know, O husband, whether you will save your wife?
461Co 7:17 Only, as the Lord has assigned to each one, as God has called each, in this manner let him walk. And thus I direct in all the churches.
461Co 7:18 Was any man called [already] circumcised? Let him not become uncircumcised. Has anyone been called in uncircumcision? Let him not be circumcised.
461Co 7:19 Circumcision is nothing, and uncircumcision is nothing, but [what matters is] the keeping of the commandments of God.
461Co 7:20 Let each man remain in that condition in which he was called.
461Co 7:21 Were you called while a slave? Do not worry about it; but if you are able also to become free, rather do that.
461Co 7:22 For he who was called in the Lord while a slave, is the Lord's freedman; likewise he who was called while free, is Christ's slave.
461Co 7:23 You were bought with a price; do not become slaves of men.
461Co 7:24 Brethren, let each man remain with God in that [condition] in which he was called.
461Co 7:25 Now concerning virgins I have no command of the Lord, but I give an opinion as one who by the mercy of the Lord is trustworthy.
461Co 7:26 I think then that this is good in view of the present distress, that it is good for a man to remain as he is.
461Co 7:27 Are you bound to a wife? Do not seek to be released. Are you released from a wife? Do not seek a wife.
461Co 7:28 But if you should marry, you have not sinned; and if a virgin should marry, she has not sinned. Yet such will have trouble in this life, and I am trying to spare you.
461Co 7:29 But this I say, brethren, the time has been shortened, so that from now on those who have wives should be as though they had none;
461Co 7:30 and those who weep, as though they did not weep; and those who rejoice, as though they did not rejoice; and those who buy, as though they did not possess;
461Co 7:31 and those who use the world, as though they did not make full use of it; for the form of this world is passing away.
461Co 7:32 But I want you to be free from concern. One who is unmarried is concerned about the things of the Lord, how he may please the Lord;
461Co 7:33 but one who is married is concerned about the things of the world, how he may please his wife,
461Co 7:34 and [his interests] are divided. And the woman who is unmarried, and the virgin, is concerned about the things of the Lord, that she may be holy both in body and spirit; but one who is married is concerned about the things of the world, how she may please her husband.
461Co 7:35 And this I say for your own benefit; not to put a restraint upon you, but to promote what is seemly, and [to secure] undistracted devotion to the Lord.
461Co 7:36 But if any man thinks that he is acting unbecomingly toward his virgin [daughter,] if she should be of full age, and if it must be so, let him do what he wishes, he does not sin; let her marry.
461Co 7:37 But he who stands firm in his heart, being under no constraint, but has authority over his own will, and has decided this in his own heart, to keep his own virgin [daughter,] he will do well.
461Co 7:38 So then both he who gives his own virgin [daughter] in marriage does well, and he who does not give her in marriage will do better.
461Co 7:39 A wife is bound as long as her husband lives; but if her husband is dead, she is free to be married to whom she wishes, only in the Lord.
461Co 7:40 But in my opinion she is happier if she remains as she is; and I think that I also have the Spirit of God.
461Co 8:1 Now concerning things sacrificed to idols, we know that we all have knowledge. Knowledge makes arrogant, but love edifies.
461Co 8:2 If anyone supposes that he knows anything, he has not yet known as he ought to know;
461Co 8:3 but if anyone loves God, he is known by Him.
461Co 8:4 Therefore concerning the eating of things sacrificed to idols, we know that there is no such thing as an idol in the world, and that there is no God but one.
461Co 8:5 For even if there are so-called gods whether in heaven or on earth, as indeed there are many gods and many lords,
461Co 8:6 yet for us there is [but] one God, the Father, from whom are all things, and we [exist] for Him; and one Lord, Jesus Christ, by whom are all things, and we [exist] through Him.
461Co 8:7 However not all men have this knowledge; but some, being accustomed to the idol until now, eat [food] as if it were sacrificed to an idol; and their conscience being weak is defiled.
461Co 8:8 But food will not commend us to God; we are neither the worse if we do not eat, nor the better if we do eat.
461Co 8:9 But take care lest this liberty of yours somehow become a stumbling block to the weak.
461Co 8:10 For if someone sees you, who have knowledge, dining in an idol's temple, will not his conscience, if he is weak, be strengthened to eat things sacrificed to idols?
461Co 8:11 For through your knowledge he who is weak is ruined, the brother for whose sake Christ died.
461Co 8:12 And thus, by sinning against the brethren and wounding their conscience when it is weak, you sin against Christ.
461Co 8:13 Therefore, if food causes my brother to stumble, I will never eat meat again, that I might not cause my brother to stumble.
461Co 9:1 Am I not free? Am I not an apostle? Have I not seen Jesus our Lord? Are you not my work in the Lord?
461Co 9:2 If to others I am not an apostle, at least I am to you; for you are the seal of my apostleship in the Lord.
461Co 9:3 My defense to those who examine me is this：
461Co 9:4 Do we not have a right to eat and drink?
461Co 9:5 Do we not have a right to take along a believing wife, even as the rest of the apostles, and the brothers of the Lord, and Cephas?
461Co 9:6 Or do only Barnabas and I not have a right to refrain from working?
461Co 9:7 Who at any time serves as a soldier at his own expense? Who plants a vineyard, and does not eat the fruit of it? Or who tends a flock and does not use the milk of the flock?
461Co 9:8 I am not speaking these things according to human judgment, am I? Or does not the Law also say these things?
461Co 9:9 For it is written in the Law of Moses, "YOU SHALL NOT MUZZLE THE OX WHILE HE IS THRESHING." God is not concerned about oxen, is He?
461Co 9:10 Or is He speaking altogether for our sake? Yes, for our sake it was written, because the plowman ought to plow in hope, and the thresher [to thresh] in hope of sharing [the crops.]
461Co 9:11 If we sowed spiritual things in you, is it too much if we should reap material things from you?
461Co 9:12 If others share the right over you, do we not more? Nevertheless, we did not use this right, but we endure all things, that we may cause no hindrance to the gospel of Christ.
461Co 9:13 Do you not know that those who perform sacred services eat the [food] of the temple, [and] those who attend regularly to the altar have their share with the altar?
461Co 9:14 So also the Lord directed those who proclaim the gospel to get their living from the gospel.
461Co 9:15 But I have used none of these things. And I am not writing these things that it may be done so in my case; for it would be better for me to die than have any man make my boast an empty one.
461Co 9:16 For if I preach the gospel, I have nothing to boast of, for I am under compulsion; for woe is me if I do not preach the gospel.
461Co 9:17 For if I do this voluntarily, I have a reward; but if against my will, I have a stewardship entrusted to me.
461Co 9:18 What then is my reward? That, when I preach the gospel, I may offer the gospel without charge, so as not to make full use of my right in the gospel.
461Co 9:19 For though I am free from all [men,] I have made myself a slave to all, that I might win the more.
461Co 9:20 And to the Jews I became as a Jew, that I might win Jews; to those who are under the Law, as under the Law, though not being myself under the Law, that I might win those who are under the Law;
461Co 9:21 to those who are without law, as without law, though not being without the law of God but under the law of Christ, that I might win those who are without law.
461Co 9:22 To the weak I became weak, that I might win the weak; I have become all things to all men, that I may by all means save some.
461Co 9:23 And I do all things for the sake of the gospel, that I may become a fellow partaker of it.
461Co 9:24 Do you not know that those who run in a race all run, but [only] one receives the prize? Run in such a way that you may win.
461Co 9:25 And everyone who competes in the games exercises self-control in all things. They then [do it] to receive a perishable wreath, but we an imperishable.
461Co 9:26 Therefore I run in such a way, as not without aim; I box in such a way, as not beating the air;
461Co 9:27 but I buffet my body and make it my slave, lest possibly, after I have preached to others, I myself should be disqualified.
461Co 10:1 For I do not want you to be unaware, brethren, that our fathers were all under the cloud, and all passed through the sea;
461Co 10:2 and all were baptized into Moses in the cloud and in the sea;
461Co 10:3 and all ate the same spiritual food;
461Co 10:4 and all drank the same spiritual drink, for they were drinking from a spiritual rock which followed them; and the rock was Christ.
461Co 10:5 Nevertheless, with most of them God was not well-pleased; for they were laid low in the wilderness.
461Co 10:6 Now these things happened as examples for us, that we should not crave evil things, as they also craved.
461Co 10:7 And do not be idolaters, as some of them were; as it is written, " THE PEOPLE SAT DOWN TO EAT AND DRINK, AND STOOD UP TO PLAY. "
461Co 10:8 Nor let us act immorally, as some of them did, and twenty-three thousand fell in one day.
461Co 10:9 Nor let us try the Lord, as some of them did, and were destroyed by the serpents.
461Co 10:10 Nor grumble, as some of them did, and were destroyed by the destroyer.
461Co 10:11 Now these things happened to them as an example, and they were written for our instruction, upon whom the ends of the ages have come.
461Co 10:12 Therefore let him who thinks he stands take heed lest he fall.
461Co 10:13 No temptation has overtaken you but such as is common to man; and God is faithful, who will not allow you to be tempted beyond what you are able, but with the temptation will provide the way of escape also, that you may be able to endure it.
461Co 10:14 Therefore, my beloved, flee from idolatry.
461Co 10:15 I speak as to wise men; you judge what I say.
461Co 10:16 Is not the cup of blessing which we bless a sharing in the blood of Christ? Is not the bread which we break a sharing in the body of Christ?
461Co 10:17 Since there is one bread, we who are many are one body; for we all partake of the one bread.
461Co 10:18 Look at the nation Israel; are not those who eat the sacrifices sharers in the altar?
461Co 10:19 What do I mean then? That a thing sacrificed to idols is anything, or that an idol is anything?
461Co 10:20 [No,] but [I say] that the things which the Gentiles sacrifice, they sacrifice to demons, and not to God; and I do not want you to become sharers in demons.
461Co 10:21 You cannot drink the cup of the Lord and the cup of demons; you cannot partake of the table of the Lord and the table of demons.
461Co 10:22 Or do we provoke the Lord to jealousy? We are not stronger than He, are we?
461Co 10:23 All things are lawful, but not all things are profitable. All things are lawful, but not all things edify.
461Co 10:24 Let no one seek his own [good,] but that of his neighbor.
461Co 10:25 Eat anything that is sold in the meat market, without asking questions for conscience' sake;
461Co 10:26 FOR THE EARTH IS THE Lord's, AND ALL IT CONTAINS.
461Co 10:27 If one of the unbelievers invites you, and you wish to go, eat anything that is set before you, without asking questions for conscience' sake.
461Co 10:28 But if anyone should say to you, "This is meat sacrificed to idols," do not eat [it,] for the sake of the one who informed [you,] and for conscience' sake;
461Co 10:29 I mean not your own conscience, but the other [man's]; for why is my freedom judged by another's conscience?
461Co 10:30 If I partake with thankfulness, why am I slandered concerning that for which I give thanks?
461Co 10:31 Whether, then, you eat or drink or whatever you do, do all to the glory of God.
461Co 10:32 Give no offense either to Jews or to Greeks or to the church of God;
461Co 10:33 just as I also please all men in all things, not seeking my own profit, but the [profit] of the many, that they may be saved.
461Co 11:1 Be imitators of me, just as I also am of Christ.
461Co 11:2 Now I praise you because you remember me in everything, and hold firmly to the traditions, just as I delivered them to you.
461Co 11:3 But I want you to understand that Christ is the head of every man, and the man is the head of a woman, and God is the head of Christ.
461Co 11:4 Every man who has [something] on his head while praying or prophesying, disgraces his head.
461Co 11:5 But every woman who has her head uncovered while praying or prophesying, disgraces her head; for she is one and the same with her whose head is shaved.
461Co 11:6 For if a woman does not cover her head, let her also have her hair cut off; but if it is disgraceful for a woman to have her hair cut off or her head shaved, let her cover her head.
461Co 11:7 For a man ought not to have his head covered, since he is the image and glory of God; but the woman is the glory of man.
461Co 11:8 For man does not originate from woman, but woman from man;
461Co 11:9 for indeed man was not created for the woman's sake, but woman for the man's sake.
461Co 11:10 Therefore the woman ought to have [a symbol of] authority on her head, because of the angels.
461Co 11:11 However, in the Lord, neither is woman independent of man, nor is man independent of woman.
461Co 11:12 For as the woman originates from the man, so also the man [has his birth] through the woman; and all things originate from God.
461Co 11:13 Judge for yourselves： is it proper for a woman to pray to God [with head] uncovered?
461Co 11:14 Does not even nature itself teach you that if a man has long hair, it is a dishonor to him,
461Co 11:15 but if a woman has long hair, it is a glory to her? For her hair is given to her for a covering.
461Co 11:16 But if one is inclined to be contentious, we have no other practice, nor have the churches of God.
461Co 11:17 But in giving this instruction, I do not praise you, because you come together not for the better but for the worse.
461Co 11:18 For, in the first place, when you come together as a church, I hear that divisions exist among you; and in part, I believe it.
461Co 11:19 For there must also be factions among you, in order that those who are approved may have become evident among you.
461Co 11:20 Therefore when you meet together, it is not to eat the Lord's Supper,
461Co 11:21 for in your eating each one takes his own supper first; and one is hungry and another is drunk.
461Co 11:22 What! Do you not have houses in which to eat and drink? Or do you despise the church of God, and shame those who have nothing? What shall I say to you? Shall I praise you? In this I will not praise you.
461Co 11:23 For I received from the Lord that which I also delivered to you, that the Lord Jesus in the night in which He was betrayed took bread;
461Co 11:24 and when He had given thanks, He broke it, and said, "This is My body, which is for you; do this in remembrance of Me."
461Co 11:25 In the same way [He took] the cup also, after supper, saying, "This cup is the new covenant in My blood; do this, as often as you drink [it,] in remembrance of Me."
461Co 11:26 For as often as you eat this bread and drink the cup, you proclaim the Lord's death until He comes.
461Co 11:27 Therefore whoever eats the bread or drinks the cup of the Lord in an unworthy manner, shall be guilty of the body and the blood of the Lord.
461Co 11:28 But let a man examine himself, and so let him eat of the bread and drink of the cup.
461Co 11:29 For he who eats and drinks, eats and drinks judgment to himself, if he does not judge the body rightly.
461Co 11:30 For this reason many among you are weak and sick, and a number sleep.
461Co 11:31 But if we judged ourselves rightly, we should not be judged.
461Co 11:32 But when we are judged, we are disciplined by the Lord in order that we may not be condemned along with the world.
461Co 11:33 So then, my brethren, when you come together to eat, wait for one another.
461Co 11:34 If anyone is hungry, let him eat at home, so that you may not come together for judgment. And the remaining matters I shall arrange when I come.
461Co 12:1 Now concerning spiritual [gifts,] brethren, I do not want you to be unaware.
461Co 12:2 You know that when you were pagans, [you were] led astray to the dumb idols, however you were led.
461Co 12:3 Therefore I make known to you, that no one speaking by the Spirit of God says, "Jesus is accursed"; and no one can say, "Jesus is Lord," except by the Holy Spirit.
461Co 12:4 Now there are varieties of gifts, but the same Spirit.
461Co 12:5 And there are varieties of ministries, and the same Lord.
461Co 12:6 And there are varieties of effects, but the same God who works all things in all [persons.]
461Co 12:7 But to each one is given the manifestation of the Spirit for the common good.
461Co 12:8 For to one is given the word of wisdom through the Spirit, and to another the word of knowledge according to the same Spirit;
461Co 12:9 to another faith by the same Spirit, and to another gifts of healing by the one Spirit,
461Co 12:10 and to another the effecting of miracles, and to another prophecy, and to another the distinguishing of spirits, to another [various] kinds of tongues, and to another the interpretation of tongues.
461Co 12:11 But one and the same Spirit works all these things, distributing to each one individually just as He wills.
461Co 12:12 For even as the body is one and [yet] has many members, and all the members of the body, though they are many, are one body, so also is Christ.
461Co 12:13 For by one Spirit we were all baptized into one body, whether Jews or Greeks, whether slaves or free, and we were all made to drink of one Spirit.
461Co 12:14 For the body is not one member, but many.
461Co 12:15 If the foot should say, "Because I am not a hand, I am not [a part] of the body," it is not for this reason any the less [a part] of the body.
461Co 12:16 And if the ear should say, "Because I am not an eye, I am not [a part] of the body," it is not for this reason any the less [a part] of the body.
461Co 12:17 If the whole body were an eye, where would the hearing be? If the whole were hearing, where would the sense of smell be?
461Co 12:18 But now God has placed the members, each one of them, in the body, just as He desired.
461Co 12:19 And if they were all one member, where would the body be?
461Co 12:20 But now there are many members, but one body.
461Co 12:21 And the eye cannot say to the hand, "I have no need of you"; or again the head to the feet, "I have no need of you."
461Co 12:22 On the contrary, it is much truer that the members of the body which seem to be weaker are necessary;
461Co 12:23 and those [members] of the body, which we deem less honorable, on these we bestow more abundant honor, and our unseemly [members come to] have more abundant seemliness,
461Co 12:24 whereas our seemly [members] have no need [of it.] But God has [so] composed the body, giving more abundant honor to that [member] which lacked,
461Co 12:25 that there should be no division in the body, but [that] the members should have the same care for one another.
461Co 12:26 And if one member suffers, all the members suffer with it; if [one] member is honored, all the members rejoice with it.
461Co 12:27 Now you are Christ's body, and individually members of it.
461Co 12:28 And God has appointed in the church, first apostles, second prophets, third teachers, then miracles, then gifts of healings, helps, administrations, [various] kinds of tongues.
461Co 12:29 All are not apostles, are they? All are not prophets, are they? All are not teachers, are they? All are not [workers of] miracles, are they?
461Co 12:30 All do not have gifts of healings, do they? All do not speak with tongues, do they? All do not interpret, do they?
461Co 12:31 But earnestly desire the greater gifts. And I show you a still more excellent way.
461Co 13:1 If I speak with the tongues of men and of angels, but do not have love, I have become a noisy gong or a clanging cymbal.
461Co 13:2 And if I have [the gift of] prophecy, and know all mysteries and all knowledge; and if I have all faith, so as to remove mountains, but do not have love, I am nothing.
461Co 13:3 And if I give all my possessions to feed [the poor,] and if I deliver my body to be burned, but do not have love, it profits me nothing.
461Co 13:4 Love is patient, love is kind, [and] is not jealous; love does not brag [and] is not arrogant,
461Co 13:5 does not act unbecomingly; it does not seek its own, is not provoked, does not take into account a wrong [suffered,]
461Co 13:6 does not rejoice in unrighteousness, but rejoices with the truth;
461Co 13:7 bears all things, believes all things, hopes all things, endures all things.
461Co 13:8 Love never fails; but if [there are gifts of] prophecy, they will be done away; if [there are] tongues, they will cease; if [there is] knowledge, it will be done away.
461Co 13:9 For we know in part, and we prophesy in part;
461Co 13:10 but when the perfect comes, the partial will be done away.
461Co 13:11 When I was a child, I used to speak as a child, think as a child, reason as a child; when I became a man, I did away with childish things.
461Co 13:12 For now we see in a mirror dimly, but then face to face; now I know in part, but then I shall know fully just as I also have been fully known.
461Co 13:13 But now abide faith, hope, love, these three; but the greatest of these is love.
461Co 14:1 Pursue love, yet desire earnestly spiritual [gifts,] but especially that you may prophesy.
461Co 14:2 For one who speaks in a tongue does not speak to men, but to God; for no one understands, but in [his] spirit he speaks mysteries.
461Co 14:3 But one who prophesies speaks to men for edification and exhortation and consolation.
461Co 14:4 One who speaks in a tongue edifies himself; but one who prophesies edifies the church.
461Co 14:5 Now I wish that you all spoke in tongues, but [even] more that you would prophesy; and greater is one who prophesies than one who speaks in tongues, unless he interprets, so that the church may receive edifying.
461Co 14:6 But now, brethren, if I come to you speaking in tongues, what shall I profit you, unless I speak to you either by way of revelation or of knowledge or of prophecy or of teaching?
461Co 14:7 Yet [even] lifeless things, either flute or harp, in producing a sound, if they do not produce a distinction in the tones, how will it be known what is played on the flute or on the harp?
461Co 14:8 For if the bugle produces an indistinct sound, who will prepare himself for battle?
461Co 14:9 So also you, unless you utter by the tongue speech that is clear, how will it be known what is spoken? For you will be speaking into the air.
461Co 14:10 There are, perhaps, a great many kinds of languages in the world, and no [kind] is without meaning.
461Co 14:11 If then I do not know the meaning of the language, I shall be to the one who speaks a barbarian, and the one who speaks will be a barbarian to me.
461Co 14:12 So also you, since you are zealous of spiritual [gifts,] seek to abound for the edification of the church.
461Co 14:13 Therefore let one who speaks in a tongue pray that he may interpret.
461Co 14:14 For if I pray in a tongue, my spirit prays, but my mind is unfruitful.
461Co 14:15 What is [the outcome] then? I shall pray with the spirit and I shall pray with the mind also; I shall sing with the spirit and I shall sing with the mind also.
461Co 14:16 Otherwise if you bless in the spirit [only,] how will the one who fills the place of the ungifted say the "Amen" at your giving of thanks, since he does not know what you are saying?
461Co 14:17 For you are giving thanks well enough, but the other man is not edified.
461Co 14:18 I thank God, I speak in tongues more than you all;
461Co 14:19 however, in the church I desire to speak five words with my mind, that I may instruct others also, rather than ten thousand words in a tongue.
461Co 14:20 Brethren, do not be children in your thinking; yet in evil be babes, but in your thinking be mature.
461Co 14:21 In the Law it is written, "BY MEN OF STRANGE TONGUES AND BY THE LIPS OF STRANGERS I WILL SPEAK TO THIS PEOPLE, AND EVEN SO THEY WILL NOT LISTEN TO ME," says the Lord.
461Co 14:22 So then tongues are for a sign, not to those who believe, but to unbelievers; but prophecy [is for a sign], not to unbelievers, but to those who believe.
461Co 14:23 If therefore the whole church should assemble together and all speak in tongues, and ungifted men or unbelievers enter, will they not say that you are mad?
461Co 14:24 But if all prophesy, and an unbeliever or an ungifted man enters, he is convicted by all, he is called to account by all;
461Co 14:25 the secrets of his heart are disclosed; and so he will fall on his face and worship God, declaring that God is certainly among you.
461Co 14:26 What is [the outcome] then, brethren? When you assemble, each one has a psalm, has a teaching, has a revelation, has a tongue, has an interpretation. Let all things be done for edification.
461Co 14:27 If anyone speaks in a tongue, [it should be] by two or at the most three, and [each] in turn, and let one interpret;
461Co 14:28 but if there is no interpreter, let him keep silent in the church; and let him speak to himself and to God.
461Co 14:29 And let two or three prophets speak, and let the others pass judgment.
461Co 14:30 But if a revelation is made to another who is seated, let the first keep silent.
461Co 14:31 For you can all prophesy one by one, so that all may learn and all may be exhorted;
461Co 14:32 and the spirits of prophets are subject to prophets;
461Co 14:33 for God is not [a God] of confusion but of peace, as in all the churches of the saints.
461Co 14:34 Let the women keep silent in the churches; for they are not permitted to speak, but let them subject themselves, just as the Law also says.
461Co 14:35 And if they desire to learn anything, let them ask their own husbands at home; for it is improper for a woman to speak in church.
461Co 14:36 Was it from you that the word of God [first] went forth? Or has it come to you only?
461Co 14:37 If anyone thinks he is a prophet or spiritual, let him recognize that the things which I write to you are the Lord's commandment.
461Co 14:38 But if anyone does not recognize [this], he is not recognized.
461Co 14:39 Therefore, my brethren, desire earnestly to prophesy, and do not forbid to speak in tongues.
461Co 14:40 But let all things be done properly and in an orderly manner.
461Co 15:1 Now I make known to you, brethren, the gospel which I preached to you, which also you received, in which also you stand,
461Co 15:2 by which also you are saved, if you hold fast the word which I preached to you, unless you believed in vain.
461Co 15:3 For I delivered to you as of first importance what I also received, that Christ died for our sins according to the Scriptures,
461Co 15:4 and that He was buried, and that He was raised on the third day according to the Scriptures,
461Co 15:5 and that He appeared to Cephas, then to the twelve.
461Co 15:6 After that He appeared to more than five hundred brethren at one time, most of whom remain until now, but some have fallen asleep;
461Co 15:7 then He appeared to James, then to all the apostles;
461Co 15:8 and last of all, as it were to one untimely born, He appeared to me also.
461Co 15:9 For I am the least of the apostles, who am not fit to be called an apostle, because I persecuted the church of God.
461Co 15:10 But by the grace of God I am what I am, and His grace toward me did not prove vain; but I labored even more than all of them, yet not I, but the grace of God with me.
461Co 15:11 Whether then [it was] I or they, so we preach and so you believed.
461Co 15:12 Now if Christ is preached, that He has been raised from the dead, how do some among you say that there is no resurrection of the dead?
461Co 15:13 But if there is no resurrection of the dead, not even Christ has been raised;
461Co 15:14 and if Christ has not been raised, then our preaching is vain, your faith also is vain.
461Co 15:15 Moreover we are even found [to be] false witnesses of God, because we witnessed against God that He raised Christ, whom He did not raise, if in fact the dead are not raised.
461Co 15:16 For if the dead are not raised, not even Christ has been raised;
461Co 15:17 and if Christ has not been raised, your faith is worthless; you are still in your sins.
461Co 15:18 Then those also who have fallen asleep in Christ have perished.
461Co 15:19 If we have hoped in Christ in this life only, we are of all men most to be pitied.
461Co 15:20 But now Christ has been raised from the dead, the first fruits of those who are asleep.
461Co 15:21 For since by a man [came] death, by a man also [came] the resurrection of the dead.
461Co 15:22 For as in Adam all die, so also in Christ all shall be made alive.
461Co 15:23 But each in his own order： Christ the first fruits, after that those who are Christ's at His coming,
461Co 15:24 then [comes] the end, when He delivers up the kingdom to the God and Father, when He has abolished all rule and all authority and power.
461Co 15:25 For He must reign until He has put all His enemies under His feet.
461Co 15:26 The last enemy that will be abolished is death.
461Co 15:27 For HE HAS PUT ALL THINGS IN SUBJECTION UNDER HIS FEET. But when He says, "All things are put in subjection," it is evident that He is excepted who put all things in subjection to Him.
461Co 15:28 And when all things are subjected to Him, then the Son Himself also will be subjected to the One who subjected all things to Him, that God may be all in all.
461Co 15:29 Otherwise, what will those do who are baptized for the dead? If the dead are not raised at all, why then are they baptized for them?
461Co 15:30 Why are we also in danger every hour?
461Co 15:31 I protest, brethren, by the boasting in you, which I have in Christ Jesus our Lord, I die daily.
461Co 15:32 If from human motives I fought with wild beasts at Ephesus, what does it profit me? If the dead are not raised, LET US EAT AND DRINK, FOR TOMORROW WE DIE.
461Co 15:33 Do not be deceived： "Bad company corrupts good morals."
461Co 15:34 Become sober-minded as you ought, and stop sinning; for some have no knowledge of God. I speak [this] to your shame.
461Co 15:35 But someone will say, "How are the dead raised? And with what kind of body do they come?"
461Co 15:36 You fool! That which you sow does not come to life unless it dies;
461Co 15:37 and that which you sow, you do not sow the body which is to be, but a bare grain, perhaps of wheat or of something else.
461Co 15:38 But God gives it a body just as He wished, and to each of the seeds a body of its own.
461Co 15:39 All flesh is not the same flesh, but there is one [flesh] of men, and another flesh of beasts, and another flesh of birds, and another of fish.
461Co 15:40 There are also heavenly bodies and earthly bodies, but the glory of the heavenly is one, and the [glory] of the earthly is another.
461Co 15:41 There is one glory of the sun, and another glory of the moon, and another glory of the stars; for star differs from star in glory.
461Co 15:42 So also is the resurrection of the dead. It is sown a perishable [ body], it is raised an imperishable [body];
461Co 15:43 it is sown in dishonor, it is raised in glory; it is sown in weakness, it is raised in power;
461Co 15:44 it is sown a natural body, it is raised a spiritual body. If there is a natural body, there is also a spiritual [body.]
461Co 15:45 So also it is written, "The first MAN, Adam, BECAME A LIVING SOUL." The last Adam [became] a life-giving spirit.
461Co 15:46 However, the spiritual is not first, but the natural; then the spiritual.
461Co 15:47 The first man is from the earth, earthy; the second man is from heaven.
461Co 15:48 As is the earthy, so also are those who are earthy; and as is the heavenly, so also are those who are heavenly.
461Co 15:49 And just as we have borne the image of the earthy, we shall also bear the image of the heavenly.
461Co 15:50 Now I say this, brethren, that flesh and blood cannot inherit the kingdom of God; nor does the perishable inherit the imperishable.
461Co 15:51 Behold, I tell you a mystery; we shall not all sleep, but we shall all be changed,
461Co 15:52 in a moment, in the twinkling of an eye, at the last trumpet; for the trumpet will sound, and the dead will be raised imperishable, and we shall be changed.
461Co 15:53 For this perishable must put on the imperishable, and this mortal must put on immortality.
461Co 15:54 But when this perishable will have put on the imperishable, and this mortal will have put on immortality, then will come about the saying that is written, "DEATH IS SWALLOWED UP in victory.
461Co 15:55 "O DEATH, WHERE IS YOUR VICTORY? O DEATH, WHERE IS YOUR STING?"
461Co 15:56 The sting of death is sin, and the power of sin is the law;
461Co 15:57 but thanks be to God, who gives us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ.
461Co 15:58 Therefore, my beloved brethren, be steadfast, immovable, always abounding in the work of the Lord, knowing that your toil is not [in] vain in the Lord.
461Co 16:1 Now concerning the collection for the saints, as I directed the churches of Galatia, so do you also.
461Co 16:2 On the first day of every week let each one of you put aside and save, as he may prosper, that no collections be made when I come.
461Co 16:3 And when I arrive, whomever you may approve, I shall send them with letters to carry your gift to Jerusalem;
461Co 16:4 and if it is fitting for me to go also, they will go with me.
461Co 16:5 But I shall come to you after I go through Macedonia, for I am going through Macedonia;
461Co 16:6 and perhaps I shall stay with you, or even spend the winter, that you may send me on my way wherever I may go.
461Co 16:7 For I do not wish to see you now [just] in passing; for I hope to remain with you for some time, if the Lord permits.
461Co 16:8 But I shall remain in Ephesus until Pentecost;
461Co 16:9 for a wide door for effective [service] has opened to me, and there are many adversaries.
461Co 16:10 Now if Timothy comes, see that he is with you without cause to be afraid; for he is doing the Lord's work, as I also am.
461Co 16:11 Let no one therefore despise him. But send him on his way in peace, so that he may come to me; for I expect him with the brethren.
461Co 16:12 But concerning Apollos our brother, I encouraged him greatly to come to you with the brethren; and it was not at all [his] desire to come now, but he will come when he has opportunity.
461Co 16:13 Be on the alert, stand firm in the faith, act like men, be strong.
461Co 16:14 Let all that you do be done in love.
461Co 16:15 Now I urge you, brethren (you know the household of Stephanas, that they were the first fruits of Achaia, and that they have devoted themselves for ministry to the saints),
461Co 16:16 that you also be in subjection to such men and to everyone who helps in the work and labors.
461Co 16:17 And I rejoice over the coming of Stephanas and Fortunatus and Achaicus; because they have supplied what was lacking on your part.
461Co 16:18 For they have refreshed my spirit and yours. Therefore acknowledge such men.
461Co 16:19 The churches of Asia greet you. Aquila and Prisca greet you heartily in the Lord, with the church that is in their house.
461Co 16:20 All the brethren greet you. Greet one another with a holy kiss.
461Co 16:21 The greeting is in my own hand-- Paul.
461Co 16:22 If anyone does not love the Lord, let him be accursed. Maranatha.
461Co 16:23 The grace of the Lord Jesus be with you.
461Co 16:24 My love be with you all in Christ Jesus. Amen.
