472Co 7:1 Therefore, having these promises, beloved, let us cleanse ourselves from all defilement of flesh and spirit, perfecting holiness in the fear of God.
472Co 7:2 Make room for us [in your hearts;] we wronged no one, we corrupted no one, we took advantage of no one.
472Co 7:3 I do not speak to condemn you; for I have said before that you are in our hearts to die together and to live together.
472Co 7:4 Great is my confidence in you, great is my boasting on your behalf; I am filled with comfort. I am overflowing with joy in all our affliction.
472Co 7:5 For even when we came into Macedonia our flesh had no rest, but we were afflicted on every side： conflicts without, fears within.
472Co 7:6 But God, who comforts the depressed, comforted us by the coming of Titus;
472Co 7:7 and not only by his coming, but also by the comfort with which he was comforted in you, as he reported to us your longing, your mourning, your zeal for me; so that I rejoiced even more.
472Co 7:8 For though I caused you sorrow by my letter, I do not regret it; though I did regret it-- [for] I see that that letter caused you sorrow, though only for a while--
472Co 7:9 I now rejoice, not that you were made sorrowful, but that you were made sorrowful to [the point of] repentance; for you were made sorrowful according to [the will of] God, in order that you might not suffer loss in anything through us.
472Co 7:10 For the sorrow that is according to [the will of] God produces a repentance without regret, [leading] to salvation; but the sorrow of the world produces death.
472Co 7:11 For behold what earnestness this very thing, this godly sorrow, has produced in you： what vindication of yourselves, what indignation, what fear, what longing, what zeal, what avenging of wrong! In everything you demonstrated yourselves to be innocent in the matter.
472Co 7:12 So although I wrote to you [it was] not for the sake of the offender, nor for the sake of the one offended, but that your earnestness on our behalf might be made known to you in the sight of God.
472Co 7:13 For this reason we have been comforted. And besides our comfort, we rejoiced even much more for the joy of Titus, because his spirit has been refreshed by you all.
472Co 7:14 For if in anything I have boasted to him about you, I was not put to shame; but as we spoke all things to you in truth, so also our boasting before Titus proved to be [the] truth.
472Co 7:15 And his affection abounds all the more toward you, as he remembers the obedience of you all, how you received him with fear and trembling.
472Co 7:16 I rejoice that in everything I have confidence in you.
472Co 8:1 Now, brethren, we [wish to] make known to you the grace of God which has been given in the churches of Macedonia,
472Co 8:2 that in a great ordeal of affliction their abundance of joy and their deep poverty overflowed in the wealth of their liberality.
472Co 8:3 For I testify that according to their ability, and beyond their ability [they gave] of their own accord,
472Co 8:4 begging us with much entreaty for the favor of participation in the support of the saints,
472Co 8:5 and [this,] not as we had expected, but they first gave themselves to the Lord and to us by the will of God.
472Co 8:6 Consequently we urged Titus that as he had previously made a beginning, so he would also complete in you this gracious work as well.
472Co 8:7 But just as you abound in everything, in faith and utterance and knowledge and in all earnestness and in the love we inspired in you, [see] that you abound in this gracious work also.
472Co 8:8 I am not speaking [this] as a command, but as proving through the earnestness of others the sincerity of your love also.
472Co 8:9 For you know the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ, that though He was rich, yet for your sake He became poor, that you through His poverty might become rich.
472Co 8:10 And I give [my] opinion in this matter, for this is to your advantage, who were the first to begin a year ago not only to do [this,] but also to desire [to do it.]
472Co 8:11 But now finish doing it also; that just as [there was] the readiness to desire it, so [there may be] also the completion of it by your ability.
472Co 8:12 For if the readiness is present, it is acceptable according to what [a man] has, not according to what he does not have.
472Co 8:13 For [this] is not for the ease of others [and] for your affliction, but by way of equality--
472Co 8:14 at this present time your abundance [being a supply] for their want, that their abundance also may become [a supply] for your want, that there may be equality;
472Co 8:15 as it is written, "HE WHO [gathered] MUCH DID NOT HAVE TOO MUCH, AND HE WHO [gathered] LITTLE HAD NO LACK."
472Co 8:16 But thanks be to God, who puts the same earnestness on your behalf in the heart of Titus.
472Co 8:17 For he not only accepted our appeal, but being himself very earnest, he has gone to you of his own accord.
472Co 8:18 And we have sent along with him the brother whose fame in [the things of] the gospel [has spread] through all the churches;
472Co 8:19 and not only [this,] but he has also been appointed by the churches to travel with us in this gracious work, which is being administered by us for the glory of the Lord Himself, and [to show] our readiness,
472Co 8:20 taking precaution that no one should discredit us in our administration of this generous gift;
472Co 8:21 for we have regard for what is honorable, not only in the sight of the Lord, but also in the sight of men.
472Co 8:22 And we have sent with them our brother, whom we have often tested and found diligent in many things, but now even more diligent, because of [his] great confidence in you.
472Co 8:23 As for Titus, [he is] my partner and fellow worker among you; as for our brethren, [they are] messengers of the churches, a glory to Christ.
472Co 8:24 Therefore openly before the churches show them the proof of your love and of our reason for boasting about you.
472Co 9:1 For it is superfluous for me to write to you about this ministry to the saints;
472Co 9:2 for I know your readiness, of which I boast about you to the Macedonians, [namely,] that Achaia has been prepared since last year, and your zeal has stirred up most of them.
472Co 9:3 But I have sent the brethren, that our boasting about you may not be made empty in this case, that, as I was saying, you may be prepared;
472Co 9:4 lest if any Macedonians come with me and find you unprepared, we (not to speak of you) should be put to shame by this confidence.
472Co 9:5 So I thought it necessary to urge the brethren that they would go on ahead to you and arrange beforehand your previously promised bountiful gift, that the same might be ready as a bountiful gift, and not affected by covetousness.
472Co 9:6 Now this [I say,] he who sows sparingly shall also reap sparingly; and he who sows bountifully shall also reap bountifully.
472Co 9:7 Let each one [do] just as he has purposed in his heart; not grudgingly or under compulsion; for God loves a cheerful giver.
472Co 9:8 And God is able to make all grace abound to you, that always having all sufficiency in everything, you may have an abundance for every good deed;
472Co 9:9 as it is written, "HE SCATTERED ABROAD, HE GAVE TO THE POOR, HIS RIGHTEOUSNESS ABIDES FOREVER."
472Co 9:10 Now He who supplies seed to the sower and bread for food, will supply and multiply your seed for sowing and increase the harvest of your righteousness;
472Co 9:11 you will be enriched in everything for all liberality, which through us is producing thanksgiving to God.
472Co 9:12 For the ministry of this service is not only fully supplying the needs of the saints, but is also overflowing through many thanksgivings to God.
472Co 9:13 Because of the proof given by this ministry they will glorify God for [your] obedience to your confession of the gospel of Christ, and for the liberality of your contribution to them and to all,
472Co 9:14 while they also, by prayer on your behalf, yearn for you because of the surpassing grace of God in you.
472Co 9:15 Thanks be to God for His indescribable gift!
472Co 10:1 Now I, Paul, myself urge you by the meekness and gentleness of Christ-- I who am meek when face to face with you, but bold toward you when absent!
472Co 10:2 I ask that when I am present I may not be bold with the confidence with which I propose to be courageous against some, who regard us as if we walked according to the flesh.
472Co 10:3 For though we walk in the flesh, we do not war according to the flesh,
472Co 10:4 for the weapons of our warfare are not of the flesh, but divinely powerful for the destruction of fortresses.
472Co 10:5 [We are] destroying speculations and every lofty thing raised up against the knowledge of God, and [we are] taking every thought captive to the obedience of Christ,
472Co 10:6 and we are ready to punish all disobedience, whenever your obedience is complete.
472Co 10:7 You are looking at things as they are outwardly. If anyone is confident in himself that he is Christ's, let him consider this again within himself, that just as he is Christ's, so also are we.
472Co 10:8 For even if I should boast somewhat further about our authority, which the Lord gave for building you up and not for destroying you, I shall not be put to shame,
472Co 10:9 for I do not wish to seem as if I would terrify you by my letters.
472Co 10:10 For they say, "His letters are weighty and strong, but his personal presence is unimpressive, and his speech contemptible."
472Co 10:11 Let such a person consider this, that what we are in word by letters when absent, such persons [we are] also in deed when present.
472Co 10:12 For we are not bold to class or compare ourselves with some of those who commend themselves; but when they measure themselves by themselves, and compare themselves with themselves, they are without understanding.
472Co 10:13 But we will not boast beyond [our] measure, but within the measure of the sphere which God apportioned to us as a measure, to reach even as far as you.
472Co 10:14 For we are not overextending ourselves, as if we did not reach to you, for we were the first to come even as far as you in the gospel of Christ;
472Co 10:15 not boasting beyond [our] measure, [that is,] in other men's labors, but with the hope that as your faith grows, we shall be, within our sphere, enlarged even more by you,
472Co 10:16 so as to preach the gospel even to the regions beyond you, [and] not to boast in what has been accomplished in the sphere of another.
472Co 10:17 But HE WHO BOASTS, LET HIM BOAST IN THE LORD.
472Co 10:18 For not he who commends himself is approved, but whom the Lord commends.
472Co 11:1 I wish that you would bear with me in a little foolishness; but indeed you are bearing with me.
472Co 11:2 For I am jealous for you with a godly jealousy; for I betrothed you to one husband, that to Christ I might present you [as] a pure virgin.
472Co 11:3 But I am afraid, lest as the serpent deceived Eve by his craftiness, your minds should be led astray from the simplicity and purity [ of devotion] to Christ.
472Co 11:4 For if one comes and preaches another Jesus whom we have not preached, or you receive a different spirit which you have not received, or a different gospel which you have not accepted, you bear [this] beautifully.
472Co 11:5 For I consider myself not in the least inferior to the most eminent apostles.
472Co 11:6 But even if I am unskilled in speech, yet I am not [so] in knowledge; in fact, in every way we have made [this] evident to you in all things.
472Co 11:7 Or did I commit a sin in humbling myself that you might be exalted, because I preached the gospel of God to you without charge?
472Co 11:8 I robbed other churches, taking wages [from them] to serve you;
472Co 11:9 and when I was present with you and was in need, I was not a burden to anyone; for when the brethren came from Macedonia, they fully supplied my need, and in everything I kept myself from being a burden to you, and will continue to do so.
472Co 11:10 As the truth of Christ is in me, this boasting of mine will not be stopped in the regions of Achaia.
472Co 11:11 Why? Because I do not love you? God knows [I do!]
472Co 11:12 But what I am doing, I will continue to do, that I may cut off opportunity from those who desire an opportunity to be regarded just as we are in the matter about which they are boasting.
472Co 11:13 For such men are false apostles, deceitful workers, disguising themselves as apostles of Christ.
472Co 11:14 And no wonder, for even Satan disguises himself as an angel of light.
472Co 11:15 Therefore it is not surprising if his servants also disguise themselves as servants of righteousness; whose end shall be according to their deeds.
472Co 11:16 Again I say, let no one think me foolish; but if [you do,] receive me even as foolish, that I also may boast a little.
472Co 11:17 That which I am speaking, I am not speaking as the Lord would, but as in foolishness, in this confidence of boasting.
472Co 11:18 Since many boast according to the flesh, I will boast also.
472Co 11:19 For you, being [so] wise, bear with the foolish gladly.
472Co 11:20 For you bear with anyone if he enslaves you, if he devours you, if he takes advantage of you, if he exalts himself, if he hits you in the face.
472Co 11:21 To [my] shame I [must] say that we have been weak [by comparison.] But in whatever respect anyone [else] is bold (I speak in foolishness), I am just as bold myself.
472Co 11:22 Are they Hebrews? So am I. Are they Israelites? So am I. Are they descendants of Abraham? So am I.
472Co 11:23 Are they servants of Christ? (I speak as if insane) I more so; in far more labors, in far more imprisonments, beaten times without number, often in danger of death.
472Co 11:24 Five times I received from the Jews thirty-nine [lashes.]
472Co 11:25 Three times I was beaten with rods, once I was stoned, three times I was shipwrecked, a night and a day I have spent in the deep.
472Co 11:26 [I have been] on frequent journeys, in dangers from rivers, dangers from robbers, dangers from [my] countrymen, dangers from the Gentiles, dangers in the city, dangers in the wilderness, dangers on the sea, dangers among false brethren;
472Co 11:27 [I have been] in labor and hardship, through many sleepless nights, in hunger and thirst, often without food, in cold and exposure.
472Co 11:28 Apart from [such] external things, there is the daily pressure upon me [of] concern for all the churches.
472Co 11:29 Who is weak without my being weak? Who is led into sin without my intense concern?
472Co 11:30 If I have to boast, I will boast of what pertains to my weakness.
472Co 11:31 The God and Father of the Lord Jesus, He who is blessed forever, knows that I am not lying.
472Co 11:32 In Damascus the ethnarch under Aretas the king was guarding the city of the Damascenes in order to seize me,
472Co 11:33 and I was let down in a basket through a window in the wall, and [ so] escaped his hands.
472Co 12:1 Boasting is necessary, though it is not profitable; but I will go on to visions and revelations of the Lord.
472Co 12:2 I know a man in Christ who fourteen years ago-- whether in the body I do not know, or out of the body I do not know, God knows-- such a man was caught up to the third heaven.
472Co 12:3 And I know how such a man-- whether in the body or apart from the body I do not know, God knows--
472Co 12:4 was caught up into Paradise, and heard inexpressible words, which a man is not permitted to speak.
472Co 12:5 On behalf of such a man will I boast; but on my own behalf I will not boast, except in regard to [my] weaknesses.
472Co 12:6 For if I do wish to boast I shall not be foolish, for I shall be speaking the truth; but I refrain [from this,] so that no one may credit me with more than he sees [in] me or hears from me.
472Co 12:7 And because of the surpassing greatness of the revelations, for this reason, to keep me from exalting myself, there was given me a thorn in the flesh, a messenger of Satan to buffet me-- to keep me from exalting myself!
472Co 12:8 Concerning this I entreated the Lord three times that it might depart from me.
472Co 12:9 And He has said to me, "My grace is sufficient for you, for power is perfected in weakness." Most gladly, therefore, I will rather boast about my weaknesses, that the power of Christ may dwell in me.
472Co 12:10 Therefore I am well content with weaknesses, with insults, with distresses, with persecutions, with difficulties, for Christ's sake; for when I am weak, then I am strong.
472Co 12:11 I have become foolish; you yourselves compelled me. Actually I should have been commended by you, for in no respect was I inferior to the most eminent apostles, even though I am a nobody.
472Co 12:12 The signs of a true apostle were performed among you with all perseverance, by signs and wonders and miracles.
472Co 12:13 For in what respect were you treated as inferior to the rest of the churches, except that I myself did not become a burden to you? Forgive me this wrong!
472Co 12:14 Here for this third time I am ready to come to you, and I will not be a burden to you; for I do not seek what is yours, but you; for children are not responsible to save up for [their] parents, but parents for [their] children.
472Co 12:15 And I will most gladly spend and be expended for your souls. If I love you the more, am I to be loved the less?
472Co 12:16 But be that as it may, I did not burden you myself; nevertheless, crafty fellow that I am, I took you in by deceit.
472Co 12:17 [Certainly] I have not taken advantage of you through any of those whom I have sent to you, have I?
472Co 12:18 I urged Titus [to go,] and sent the brother with him. Titus did not take any advantage of you, did he? Did we not conduct ourselves in the same spirit [and walk] in the same steps?
472Co 12:19 All this time you have been thinking that we are defending ourselves to you. [Actually,] it is in the sight of God that we have been speaking in Christ; and all for your upbuilding, beloved.
472Co 12:20 For I am afraid that perhaps when I come I may find you to be not what I wish and may be found by you to be not what you wish; that perhaps [there may be] strife, jealousy, angry tempers, disputes, slanders, gossip, arrogance, disturbances;
472Co 12:21 I am afraid that when I come again my God may humiliate me before you, and I may mourn over many of those who have sinned in the past and not repented of the impurity, immorality and sensuality which they have practiced.
472Co 13:1 This is the third time I am coming to you. EVERY FACT IS TO BE CONFIRMED BY THE TESTIMONY OF TWO OR THREE WITNESSES.
472Co 13:2 I have previously said when present the second time, and though now absent I say in advance to those who have sinned in the past and to all the rest as well, that if I come again, I will not spare [anyone,]
472Co 13:3 since you are seeking for proof of the Christ who speaks in me, and who is not weak toward you, but mighty in you.
472Co 13:4 For indeed He was crucified because of weakness, yet He lives because of the power of God. For we also are weak in Him, yet we shall live with Him because of the power of God [directed] toward you.
472Co 13:5 Test yourselves [to see] if you are in the faith; examine yourselves! Or do you not recognize this about yourselves, that Jesus Christ is in you-- unless indeed you fail the test?
472Co 13:6 But I trust that you will realize that we ourselves do not fail the test.
472Co 13:7 Now we pray to God that you do no wrong; not that we ourselves may appear approved, but that you may do what is right, even though we should appear unapproved.
472Co 13:8 For we can do nothing against the truth, but [only] for the truth.
472Co 13:9 For we rejoice when we ourselves are weak but you are strong; this we also pray for, that you be made complete.
472Co 13:10 For this reason I am writing these things while absent, in order that when present I may not use severity, in accordance with the authority which the Lord gave me, for building up and not for tearing down.
472Co 13:11 Finally, brethren, rejoice, be made complete, be comforted, be like-minded, live in peace; and the God of love and peace shall be with you.
472Co 13:12 Greet one another with a holy kiss.
472Co 13:13 All the saints greet you.
472Co 13:14 The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ, and the love of God, and the fellowship of the Holy Spirit, be with you all.
