48Gl 3:1 You foolish Galatians, who has bewitched you, before whose eyes Jesus Christ was publicly portrayed [as] crucified?
48Gl 3:2 This is the only thing I want to find out from you： did you receive the Spirit by the works of the Law, or by hearing with faith?
48Gl 3:3 Are you so foolish? Having begun by the Spirit, are you now being perfected by the flesh?
48Gl 3:4 Did you suffer so many things in vain-- if indeed it was in vain?
48Gl 3:5 Does He then, who provides you with the Spirit and works miracles among you, do it by the works of the Law, or by hearing with faith?
48Gl 3:6 Even so Abraham BELIEVED GOD, AND IT WAS RECKONED TO HIM AS RIGHTEOUSNESS.
48Gl 3:7 Therefore, be sure that it is those who are of faith who are sons of Abraham.
48Gl 3:8 And the Scripture, foreseeing that God would justify the Gentiles by faith, preached the gospel beforehand to Abraham, [saying], "ALL THE NATIONS SHALL BE BLESSED IN YOU."
48Gl 3:9 So then those who are of faith are blessed with Abraham, the believer.
48Gl 3:10 For as many as are of the works of the Law are under a curse; for it is written, "CURSED IS EVERYONE WHO DOES NOT ABIDE BY ALL THINGS WRITTEN IN THE BOOK OF THE LAW, TO PERFORM THEM."
48Gl 3:11 Now that no one is justified by the Law before God is evident; for, " THE RIGHTEOUS MAN SHALL LIVE BY FAITH. "
48Gl 3:12 However, the Law is not of faith; on the contrary, "HE WHO PRACTICES THEM SHALL LIVE BY THEM."
48Gl 3:13 Christ redeemed us from the curse of the Law, having become a curse for us-- for it is written, "CURSED IS EVERYONE WHO HANGS ON A TREE"- -
48Gl 3:14 in order that in Christ Jesus the blessing of Abraham might come to the Gentiles, so that we might receive the promise of the Spirit through faith.
48Gl 3:15 Brethren, I speak in terms of human relations： even though it is [ only] a man's covenant, yet when it has been ratified, no one sets it aside or adds conditions to it.
48Gl 3:16 Now the promises were spoken to Abraham and to his seed. He does not say, "And to seeds," as [referring] to many, but [rather] to one, "And to your seed," that is, Christ.
48Gl 3:17 What I am saying is this： the Law, which came four hundred and thirty years later, does not invalidate a covenant previously ratified by God, so as to nullify the promise.
48Gl 3:18 For if the inheritance is based on law, it is no longer based on a promise; but God has granted it to Abraham by means of a promise.
48Gl 3:19 Why the Law then? It was added because of transgressions, having been ordained through angels by the agency of a mediator, until the seed should come to whom the promise had been made.
48Gl 3:20 Now a mediator is not for one [party only]; whereas God is [only] one.
48Gl 3:21 Is the Law then contrary to the promises of God? May it never be! For if a law had been given which was able to impart life, then righteousness would indeed have been based on law.
48Gl 3:22 But the Scripture has shut up all men under sin, that the promise by faith in Jesus Christ might be given to those who believe.
48Gl 3:23 But before faith came, we were kept in custody under the law, being shut up to the faith which was later to be revealed.
48Gl 3:24 Therefore the Law has become our tutor [to lead us] to Christ, that we may be justified by faith.
48Gl 3:25 But now that faith has come, we are no longer under a tutor.
48Gl 3:26 For you are all sons of God through faith in Christ Jesus.
48Gl 3:27 For all of you who were baptized into Christ have clothed yourselves with Christ.
48Gl 3:28 There is neither Jew nor Greek, there is neither slave nor free man, there is neither male nor female; for you are all one in Christ Jesus.
48Gl 3:29 And if you belong to Christ, then you are Abraham's offspring, heirs according to promise.
48Gl 4:1 Now I say, as long as the heir is a child, he does not differ at all from a slave although he is owner of everything,
48Gl 4:2 but he is under guardians and managers until the date set by the father.
48Gl 4:3 So also we, while we were children, were held in bondage under the elemental things of the world.
48Gl 4:4 But when the fulness of the time came, God sent forth His Son, born of a woman, born under the Law,
48Gl 4:5 in order that He might redeem those who were under the Law, that we might receive the adoption as sons.
48Gl 4:6 And because you are sons, God has sent forth the Spirit of His Son into our hearts, crying, "Abba! Father!"
48Gl 4:7 Therefore you are no longer a slave, but a son; and if a son, then an heir through God.
48Gl 4:8 However at that time, when you did not know God, you were slaves to those which by nature are no gods.
48Gl 4:9 But now that you have come to know God, or rather to be known by God, how is it that you turn back again to the weak and worthless elemental things, to which you desire to be enslaved all over again?
48Gl 4:10 You observe days and months and seasons and years.
48Gl 4:11 I fear for you, that perhaps I have labored over you in vain.
48Gl 4:12 I beg of you, brethren, become as I [am], for I also [have become] as you [are.] You have done me no wrong;
48Gl 4:13 but you know that it was because of a bodily illness that I preached the gospel to you the first time;
48Gl 4:14 and that which was a trial to you in my bodily condition you did not despise or loathe, but you received me as an angel of God, as Christ Jesus [Himself.]
48Gl 4:15 Where then is that sense of blessing you had? For I bear you witness, that if possible, you would have plucked out your eyes and given them to me.
48Gl 4:16 Have I therefore become your enemy by telling you the truth?
48Gl 4:17 They eagerly seek you, not commendably, but they wish to shut you out, in order that you may seek them.
48Gl 4:18 But it is good always to be eagerly sought in a commendable manner, and not only when I am present with you.
48Gl 4:19 My children, with whom I am again in labor until Christ is formed in you--
48Gl 4:20 but I could wish to be present with you now and to change my tone, for I am perplexed about you.
48Gl 4:21 Tell me, you who want to be under law, do you not listen to the law?
48Gl 4:22 For it is written that Abraham had two sons, one by the bondwoman and one by the free woman.
48Gl 4:23 But the son by the bondwoman was born according to the flesh, and the son by the free woman through the promise.
48Gl 4:24 This is allegorically speaking： for these [women] are two covenants, one [proceeding] from Mount Sinai bearing children who are to be slaves; she is Hagar.
48Gl 4:25 Now this Hagar is Mount Sinai in Arabia, and corresponds to the present Jerusalem, for she is in slavery with her children.
48Gl 4:26 But the Jerusalem above is free; she is our mother.
48Gl 4:27 For it is written, "REJOICE, BARREN WOMAN WHO DOES NOT BEAR; BREAK FORTH AND SHOUT, YOU WHO ARE NOT IN LABOR; FOR MORE ARE THE CHILDREN OF THE DESOLATE THAN OF THE ONE WHO HAS A HUSBAND."
48Gl 4:28 And you brethren, like Isaac, are children of promise.
48Gl 4:29 But as at that time he who was born according to the flesh persecuted him [who was born] according to the Spirit, so it is now also.
48Gl 4:30 But what does the Scripture say? "CAST OUT THE BONDWOMAN AND HER SON, FOR THE SON OF THE BONDWOMAN SHALL NOT BE AN HEIR WITH THE SON OF THE FREE WOMAN."
48Gl 4:31 So then, brethren, we are not children of a bondwoman, but of the free woman.
48Gl 5:1 It was for freedom that Christ set us free; therefore keep standing firm and do not be subject again to a yoke of slavery.
48Gl 5:2 Behold I, Paul, say to you that if you receive circumcision, Christ will be of no benefit to you.
48Gl 5:3 And I testify again to every man who receives circumcision, that he is under obligation to keep the whole Law.
48Gl 5:4 You have been severed from Christ, you who are seeking to be justified by law; you have fallen from grace.
48Gl 5:5 For we through the Spirit, by faith, are waiting for the hope of righteousness.
48Gl 5:6 For in Christ Jesus neither circumcision nor uncircumcision means anything, but faith working through love.
48Gl 5:7 You were running well; who hindered you from obeying the truth?
48Gl 5:8 This persuasion [did] not [come] from Him who calls you.
48Gl 5:9 A little leaven leavens the whole lump [of dough.]
48Gl 5:10 I have confidence in you in the Lord, that you will adopt no other view; but the one who is disturbing you shall bear his judgment, whoever he is.
48Gl 5:11 But I, brethren, if I still preach circumcision, why am I still persecuted? Then the stumbling block of the cross has been abolished.
48Gl 5:12 Would that those who are troubling you would even mutilate themselves.
48Gl 5:13 For you were called to freedom, brethren; only [do] not [turn] your freedom into an opportunity for the flesh, but through love serve one another.
48Gl 5:14 For the whole Law is fulfilled in one word, in the [statement], " YOU SHALL LOVE YOUR NEIGHBOR AS YOURSELF. "
48Gl 5:15 But if you bite and devour one another, take care lest you be consumed by one another.
48Gl 5:16 But I say, walk by the Spirit, and you will not carry out the desire of the flesh.
48Gl 5:17 For the flesh sets its desire against the Spirit, and the Spirit against the flesh; for these are in opposition to one another, so that you may not do the things that you please.
48Gl 5:18 But if you are led by the Spirit, you are not under the Law.
48Gl 5:19 Now the deeds of the flesh are evident, which are： immorality, impurity, sensuality,
48Gl 5:20 idolatry, sorcery, enmities, strife, jealousy, outbursts of anger, disputes, dissensions, factions,
48Gl 5:21 envying, drunkenness, carousing, and things like these, of which I forewarn you just as I have forewarned you that those who practice such things shall not inherit the kingdom of God.
48Gl 5:22 But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness,
48Gl 5:23 gentleness, self-control; against such things there is no law.
48Gl 5:24 Now those who belong to Christ Jesus have crucified the flesh with its passions and desires.
48Gl 5:25 If we live by the Spirit, let us also walk by the Spirit.
48Gl 5:26 Let us not become boastful, challenging one another, envying one another.
48Gl 6:1 Brethren, even if a man is caught in any trespass, you who are spiritual, restore such a one in a spirit of gentleness; [each one] looking to yourself, lest you too be tempted.
48Gl 6:2 Bear one another's burdens, and thus fulfill the law of Christ.
48Gl 6:3 For if anyone thinks he is something when he is nothing, he deceives himself.
48Gl 6:4 But let each one examine his own work, and then he will have [reason for] boasting in regard to himself alone, and not in regard to another.
48Gl 6:5 For each one shall bear his own load.
48Gl 6:6 And let the one who is taught the word share all good things with him who teaches.
48Gl 6:7 Do not be deceived, God is not mocked; for whatever a man sows, this he will also reap.
48Gl 6:8 For the one who sows to his own flesh shall from the flesh reap corruption, but the one who sows to the Spirit shall from the Spirit reap eternal life.
48Gl 6:9 And let us not lose heart in doing good, for in due time we shall reap if we do not grow weary.
48Gl 6:10 So then, while we have opportunity, let us do good to all men, and especially to those who are of the household of the faith.
48Gl 6:11 See with what large letters I am writing to you with my own hand.
48Gl 6:12 Those who desire to make a good showing in the flesh try to compel you to be circumcised, simply that they may not be persecuted for the cross of Christ.
48Gl 6:13 For those who are circumcised do not even keep the Law themselves, but they desire to have you circumcised, that they may boast in your flesh.
48Gl 6:14 But may it never be that I should boast, except in the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ, through which the world has been crucified to me, and I to the world.
48Gl 6:15 For neither is circumcision anything, nor uncircumcision, but a new creation.
48Gl 6:16 And those who will walk by this rule, peace and mercy [be] upon them, and upon the Israel of God.
48Gl 6:17 From now on let no one cause trouble for me, for I bear on my body the brand-marks of Jesus.
48Gl 6:18 The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit, brethren. Amen.
