49Eph 4:21 if indeed you have heard Him and have been taught in Him, just as truth is in Jesus,
49Eph 4:22 that, in reference to your former manner of life, you lay aside the old self, which is being corrupted in accordance with the lusts of deceit,
49Eph 4:23 and that you be renewed in the spirit of your mind,
49Eph 4:24 and put on the new self, which in [the likeness of] God has been created in righteousness and holiness of the truth.
49Eph 4:25 Therefore, laying aside falsehood, SPEAK TRUTH, EACH ONE [of you,] WITH HIS NEIGHBOR, for we are members of one another.
49Eph 4:26 BE ANGRY, AND [yet] DO NOT SIN; do not let the sun go down on your anger,
49Eph 4:27 and do not give the devil an opportunity.
49Eph 4:28 Let him who steals steal no longer; but rather let him labor, performing with his own hands what is good, in order that he may have [something] to share with him who has need.
49Eph 4:29 Let no unwholesome word proceed from your mouth, but only such [a word] as is good for edification according to the need [of the moment,] that it may give grace to those who hear.
49Eph 4:30 And do not grieve the Holy Spirit of God, by whom you were sealed for the day of redemption.
49Eph 4:31 Let all bitterness and wrath and anger and clamor and slander be put away from you, along with all malice.
49Eph 4:32 And be kind to one another, tender-hearted, forgiving each other, just as God in Christ also has forgiven you.
49Eph 5:1 Therefore be imitators of God, as beloved children;
49Eph 5:2 and walk in love, just as Christ also loved you, and gave Himself up for us, an offering and a sacrifice to God as a fragrant aroma.
49Eph 5:3 But do not let immorality or any impurity or greed even be named among you, as is proper among saints;
49Eph 5:4 and [there must be no] filthiness and silly talk, or coarse jesting, which are not fitting, but rather giving of thanks.
49Eph 5:5 For this you know with certainty, that no immoral or impure person or covetous man, who is an idolater, has an inheritance in the kingdom of Christ and God.
49Eph 5:6 Let no one deceive you with empty words, for because of these things the wrath of God comes upon the sons of disobedience.
49Eph 5:7 Therefore do not be partakers with them;
49Eph 5:8 for you were formerly darkness, but now you are light in the Lord; walk as children of light
49Eph 5:9 (for the fruit of the light [consists] in all goodness and righteousness and truth),
49Eph 5:10 trying to learn what is pleasing to the Lord.
49Eph 5:11 And do not participate in the unfruitful deeds of darkness, but instead even expose them;
49Eph 5:12 for it is disgraceful even to speak of the things which are done by them in secret.
49Eph 5:13 But all things become visible when they are exposed by the light, for everything that becomes visible is light.
49Eph 5:14 For this reason it says, "Awake, sleeper, And arise from the dead, And Christ will shine on you."
49Eph 5:15 Therefore be careful how you walk, not as unwise men, but as wise,
49Eph 5:16 making the most of your time, because the days are evil.
49Eph 5:17 So then do not be foolish, but understand what the will of the Lord is.
49Eph 5:18 And do not get drunk with wine, for that is dissipation, but be filled with the Spirit,
49Eph 5:19 speaking to one another in psalms and hymns and spiritual songs, singing and making melody with your heart to the Lord;
49Eph 5:20 always giving thanks for all things in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ to God, even the Father;
49Eph 5:21 and be subject to one another in the fear of Christ.
