49Eph 5:23 For the husband is the head of the wife, as Christ also is the head of the church, He Himself [being] the Savior of the body.
49Eph 5:24 But as the church is subject to Christ, so also the wives [ought to be] to their husbands in everything.
49Eph 5:25 Husbands, love your wives, just as Christ also loved the church and gave Himself up for her;
49Eph 5:26 that He might sanctify her, having cleansed her by the washing of water with the word,
49Eph 5:27 that He might present to Himself the church in all her glory, having no spot or wrinkle or any such thing; but that she should be holy and blameless.
49Eph 5:28 So husbands ought also to love their own wives as their own bodies. He who loves his own wife loves himself;
49Eph 5:29 for no one ever hated his own flesh, but nourishes and cherishes it, just as Christ also [does] the church,
49Eph 5:30 because we are members of His body.
49Eph 5:31 FOR THIS CAUSE A MAN SHALL LEAVE HIS FATHER AND MOTHER, AND SHALL CLEAVE TO HIS WIFE; AND THE TWO SHALL BECOME ONE FLESH.
49Eph 5:32 This mystery is great; but I am speaking with reference to Christ and the church.
49Eph 5:33 Nevertheless let each individual among you also love his own wife even as himself; and [let] the wife [see to it] that she respect her husband.
49Eph 6:1 Children, obey your parents in the Lord, for this is right.
49Eph 6:2 HONOR YOUR FATHER AND MOTHER (which is the first commandment with a promise),
49Eph 6:3 THAT IT MAY BE WELL WITH YOU, AND THAT YOU MAY LIVE LONG ON THE EARTH.
49Eph 6:4 And, fathers, do not provoke your children to anger; but bring them up in the discipline and instruction of the Lord.
49Eph 6:5 Slaves, be obedient to those who are your masters according to the flesh, with fear and trembling, in the sincerity of your heart, as to Christ;
49Eph 6:6 not by way of eyeservice, as men-pleasers, but as slaves of Christ, doing the will of God from the heart.
