51Col 1:10 so that you may walk in a manner worthy of the Lord, to please [Him] in all respects, bearing fruit in every good work and increasing in the knowledge of God;
51Col 1:11 strengthened with all power, according to His glorious might, for the attaining of all steadfastness and patience; joyously
51Col 1:12 giving thanks to the Father, who has qualified us to share in the inheritance of the saints in light.
51Col 1:13 For He delivered us from the domain of darkness, and transferred us to the kingdom of His beloved Son,
51Col 1:14 in whom we have redemption, the forgiveness of sins.
51Col 1:15 And He is the image of the invisible God, the first-born of all creation.
51Col 1:16 For by Him all things were created, [both] in the heavens and on earth, visible and invisible, whether thrones or dominions or rulers or authorities-- all things have been created by Him and for Him.
