51Col 2:21 "Do not handle, do not taste, do not touch!"
51Col 2:22 (which all [refer to] things destined to perish with the using)-- in accordance with the commandments and teachings of men?
51Col 2:23 These are matters which have, to be sure, the appearance of wisdom in self-made religion and self-abasement and severe treatment of the body, [ but are] of no value against fleshly indulgence.
51Col 3:1 If then you have been raised up with Christ, keep seeking the things above, where Christ is, seated at the right hand of God.
51Col 3:2 Set your mind on the things above, not on the things that are on earth.
