51Col 4:1 Masters, grant to your slaves justice and fairness, knowing that you too have a Master in heaven.
51Col 4:2 Devote yourselves to prayer, keeping alert in it with [an attitude of] thanksgiving;
51Col 4:3 praying at the same time for us as well, that God may open up to us a door for the word, so that we may speak forth the mystery of Christ, for which I have also been imprisoned;
51Col 4:4 in order that I may make it clear in the way I ought to speak.
51Col 4:5 Conduct yourselves with wisdom toward outsiders, making the most of the opportunity.
