552Tm 1:1 Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus by the will of God, according to the promise of life in Christ Jesus,
552Tm 1:2 to Timothy, my beloved son： Grace, mercy [and] peace from God the Father and Christ Jesus our Lord.
552Tm 1:3 I thank God, whom I serve with a clear conscience the way my forefathers did, as I constantly remember you in my prayers night and day,
552Tm 1:4 longing to see you, even as I recall your tears, so that I may be filled with joy.
552Tm 1:5 For I am mindful of the sincere faith within you, which first dwelt in your grandmother Lois, and your mother Eunice, and I am sure that [it is] in you as well.
552Tm 1:6 And for this reason I remind you to kindle afresh the gift of God which is in you through the laying on of my hands.
552Tm 1:7 For God has not given us a spirit of timidity, but of power and love and discipline.
552Tm 1:8 Therefore do not be ashamed of the testimony of our Lord, or of me His prisoner; but join with [me] in suffering for the gospel according to the power of God,
552Tm 1:9 who has saved us, and called us with a holy calling, not according to our works, but according to His own purpose and grace which was granted us in Christ Jesus from all eternity,
552Tm 1:10 but now has been revealed by the appearing of our Savior Christ Jesus, who abolished death, and brought life and immortality to light through the gospel,
552Tm 1:11 for which I was appointed a preacher and an apostle and a teacher.
552Tm 1:12 For this reason I also suffer these things, but I am not ashamed; for I know whom I have believed and I am convinced that He is able to guard what I have entrusted to Him until that day.
552Tm 1:13 Retain the standard of sound words which you have heard from me, in the faith and love which are in Christ Jesus.
552Tm 1:14 Guard, through the Holy Spirit who dwells in us, the treasure which has been entrusted to [you.]
552Tm 1:15 You are aware of the fact that all who are in Asia turned away from me, among whom are Phygelus and Hermogenes.
552Tm 1:16 The Lord grant mercy to the house of Onesiphorus for he often refreshed me, and was not ashamed of my chains;
552Tm 1:17 but when he was in Rome, he eagerly searched for me, and found me--
552Tm 1:18 the Lord grant to him to find mercy from the Lord on that day-- and you know very well what services he rendered at Ephesus.
552Tm 2:1 You therefore, my son, be strong in the grace that is in Christ Jesus.
552Tm 2:2 And the things which you have heard from me in the presence of many witnesses, these entrust to faithful men, who will be able to teach others also.
552Tm 2:3 Suffer hardship with [me,] as a good soldier of Christ Jesus.
552Tm 2:4 No soldier in active service entangles himself in the affairs of everyday life, so that he may please the one who enlisted him as a soldier.
552Tm 2:5 And also if anyone competes as an athlete, he does not win the prize unless he competes according to the rules.
552Tm 2:6 The hard-working farmer ought to be the first to receive his share of the crops.
552Tm 2:7 Consider what I say, for the Lord will give you understanding in everything.
552Tm 2:8 Remember Jesus Christ, risen from the dead, descendant of David, according to my gospel,
552Tm 2:9 for which I suffer hardship even to imprisonment as a criminal; but the word of God is not imprisoned.
552Tm 2:10 For this reason I endure all things for the sake of those who are chosen, that they also may obtain the salvation which is in Christ Jesus [and] with [it] eternal glory.
552Tm 2:11 It is a trustworthy statement： For if we died with Him, we shall also live with Him;
552Tm 2:12 If we endure, we shall also reign with Him; If we deny Him, He also will deny us;
552Tm 2:13 If we are faithless, He remains faithful; for He cannot deny Himself.
552Tm 2:14 Remind [them] of these things, and solemnly charge [them] in the presence of God not to wrangle about words, which is useless, [and leads] to the ruin of the hearers.
552Tm 2:15 Be diligent to present yourself approved to God as a workman who does not need to be ashamed, handling accurately the word of truth.
552Tm 2:16 But avoid worldly [and] empty chatter, for it will lead to further ungodliness,
552Tm 2:17 and their talk will spread like gangrene. Among them are Hymenaeus and Philetus,
552Tm 2:18 [men] who have gone astray from the truth saying that the resurrection has already taken place, and thus they upset the faith of some.
552Tm 2:19 Nevertheless, the firm foundation of God stands, having this seal, " The Lord knows those who are His, "and," Let everyone who names the name of the Lord abstain from wickedness. "
552Tm 2:20 Now in a large house there are not only gold and silver vessels, but also vessels of wood and of earthenware, and some to honor and some to dishonor.
552Tm 2:21 Therefore, if a man cleanses himself from these [things], he will be a vessel for honor, sanctified, useful to the Master, prepared for every good work.
552Tm 2:22 Now flee from youthful lusts, and pursue righteousness, faith, love [and] peace, with those who call on the Lord from a pure heart.
552Tm 2:23 But refuse foolish and ignorant speculations, knowing that they produce quarrels.
552Tm 2:24 And the Lord's bond-servant must not be quarrelsome, but be kind to all, able to teach, patient when wronged,
552Tm 2:25 with gentleness correcting those who are in opposition, if perhaps God may grant them repentance leading to the knowledge of the truth,
552Tm 2:26 and they may come to their senses [and escape] from the snare of the devil, having been held captive by him to do his will.
552Tm 3:1 But realize this, that in the last days difficult times will come.
552Tm 3:2 For men will be lovers of self, lovers of money, boastful, arrogant, revilers, disobedient to parents, ungrateful, unholy,
552Tm 3:3 unloving, irreconcilable, malicious gossips, without self-control, brutal, haters of good,
552Tm 3:4 treacherous, reckless, conceited, lovers of pleasure rather than lovers of God;
552Tm 3:5 holding to a form of godliness, although they have denied its power; and avoid such men as these.
552Tm 3:6 For among them are those who enter into households and captivate weak women weighed down with sins, led on by various impulses,
552Tm 3:7 always learning and never able to come to the knowledge of the truth.
552Tm 3:8 And just as Jannes and Jambres opposed Moses, so these [men] also oppose the truth, men of depraved mind, rejected as regards the faith.
552Tm 3:9 But they will not make further progress; for their folly will be obvious to all, as also that of those [two] came to be.
552Tm 3:10 But you followed my teaching, conduct, purpose, faith, patience, love, perseverance,
552Tm 3:11 persecutions, [and] sufferings, such as happened to me at Antioch, at Iconium [and] at Lystra; what persecutions I endured, and out of them all the Lord delivered me!
552Tm 3:12 And indeed, all who desire to live godly in Christ Jesus will be persecuted.
552Tm 3:13 But evil men and impostors will proceed [from bad] to worse, deceiving and being deceived.
552Tm 3:14 You, however, continue in the things you have learned and become convinced of, knowing from whom you have learned [them];
552Tm 3:15 and that from childhood you have known the sacred writings which are able to give you the wisdom that leads to salvation through faith which is in Christ Jesus.
552Tm 3:16 All Scripture is inspired by God and profitable for teaching, for reproof, for correction, for training in righteousness;
552Tm 3:17 that the man of God may be adequate, equipped for every good work.
552Tm 4:1 I solemnly charge [you] in the presence of God and of Christ Jesus, who is to judge the living and the dead, and by His appearing and His kingdom：
552Tm 4:2 preach the word; be ready in season [and] out of season; reprove, rebuke, exhort, with great patience and instruction.
552Tm 4:3 For the time will come when they will not endure sound doctrine; but [wanting] to have their ears tickled, they will accumulate for themselves teachers in accordance to their own desires;
552Tm 4:4 and will turn away their ears from the truth, and will turn aside to myths.
552Tm 4:5 But you, be sober in all things, endure hardship, do the work of an evangelist, fulfill your ministry.
552Tm 4:6 For I am already being poured out as a drink offering, and the time of my departure has come.
552Tm 4:7 I have fought the good fight, I have finished the course, I have kept the faith;
552Tm 4:8 in the future there is laid up for me the crown of righteousness, which the Lord, the righteous Judge, will award to me on that day; and not only to me, but also to all who have loved His appearing.
552Tm 4:9 Make every effort to come to me soon;
552Tm 4:10 for Demas, having loved this present world, has deserted me and gone to Thessalonica; Crescens [has gone] to Galatia, Titus to Dalmatia.
552Tm 4:11 Only Luke is with me. Pick up Mark and bring him with you, for he is useful to me for service.
552Tm 4:12 But Tychicus I have sent to Ephesus.
552Tm 4:13 When you come bring the cloak which I left at Troas with Carpus, and the books, especially the parchments.
552Tm 4:14 Alexander the coppersmith did me much harm; the Lord will repay him according to his deeds.
552Tm 4:15 Be on guard against him yourself, for he vigorously opposed our teaching.
552Tm 4:16 At my first defense no one supported me, but all deserted me; may it not be counted against them.
552Tm 4:17 But the Lord stood with me, and strengthened me, in order that through me the proclamation might be fully accomplished, and that all the Gentiles might hear; and I was delivered out of the lion's mouth.
552Tm 4:18 The Lord will deliver me from every evil deed, and will bring me safely to His heavenly kingdom; to Him [be] the glory forever and ever. Amen.
552Tm 4:19 Greet Prisca and Aquila, and the household of Onesiphorus.
552Tm 4:20 Erastus remained at Corinth, but Trophimus I left sick at Miletus.
552Tm 4:21 Make every effort to come before winter. Eubulus greets you, also Pudens and Linus and Claudia and all the brethren.
552Tm 4:22 The Lord be with your spirit. Grace be with you.
